text: Aldo Eminente (19 August 1931 – 25 August 2021) was a French freestyle swimmer. He was born in Hanoi, French Indochina. He competed at the 1952 Olympic Games in Helsinki, where he won a bronze medal."1952 Olympics - Helsinki, Finland - Swimming" - databaseOlympics.com (Retrieved on 30 August 2008) Eminente died on 25 August 2021, aged 90.Aldo Eminente, médaillé aux Jeux Olympiques de 1952, est mort ==References== Category:1931 births Category:2021 deaths Category:French swimmers Category:Olympic bronze medalists for France Category:People from Hanoi
